posts.title: What do LLMs think when you don't tell them what to think about?
posts.description: What do language models generate when you don't tell them what to generate? New research reveals that LLM families have distinct 'knowledge priors'‚ÄîGPT models default to code and math, Llama favors narratives, DeepSeek generates religious content, and Qwen outputs exam questions.

posts.title: Together Evaluations now supports comparing top commercial APIs vs. open source models
posts.description: Together Evaluations now supports OpenAI, Anthropic, and Google models for cross-provider benchmarking. Compare open-source, fine-tuned, and proprietary models side-by-side to make data-driven decisions on quality, cost, and performance‚Äîall in one platform.

posts.title: Fine-tuning open LLM judges to outperform GPT-5.2
posts.description: Fine-tuned open-source LLM judges can outperform GPT-5.2 at evaluating model outputs. Using Direct Preference Optimization on just 5,400 preference pairs, we trained GPT-OSS 120B to beat GPT-5.2 on human preference alignment‚Äîat 15x lower cost and 14x faster inference speeds.

posts.title: Optimizing inference speed and costs: Lessons learned from large-scale deployments
posts.description: Learn how to reduce inference latency without massive cost using proven inference optimization tactics ‚Äî improving throughput, GPU utilization, and cost efficiency while balancing throughput vs. latency tradeoffs.

posts.title: Learn how Cursor partnered with Together AI to deliver real-time, low-latency inference at scale
posts.description: Together AI teamed with Cursor to build the real-time inference stack that keeps in-editor agents fast and reliable. They productionized NVIDIA Blackwell (B200/GB200), tuning ARM hosts, kernels, and FP4/TensorRT quantization for low latency and rapid model rollouts.
